Tharaka Nithi Governor Muthomi Njuki has accused NASA leader Raila Odinga of what he termed betrayal of the handshake between him and President Uhuru Kenyatta. Speaking while launching a dairy project in Maara Sub County, Njuki said Mr Odinga has gone against the spirit of the handshake for his selfish interests. ALSO READ:

Raila’s dalliance with Moi, Mt Kenya stirs up Nyanza He took issue with Odinga’s visit to former President Daniel Moi saying his aim was to strategise about his political future